# Why Java Uses Bit Operations

Many Java internals rely on binary operations because they are extremely fast.

Examples include:

- HashMap
- ThreadLocal
- EnumSet
- BitSet
- ConcurrentHashMap
- JVM internals
- Networking
- Compression

